1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

2
00:00:04,760 --> 00:00:06,440
 You can see two pictures here.

3
00:00:06,440 --> 00:00:09,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

4
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:11,120
 On the left is a lonely man.

5
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:14,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

6
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:18,080
 On the right is a very happy gathering family.

7
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:20,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

8
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:22,680
 And if you have a choice, which one would you pick?

9
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:23,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

10
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:25,120
 Of course, the right one.

11
00:00:25,120 --> 00:00:28,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

12
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:30,560
 We all desire to be part of the community.

13
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:33,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

14
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:34,840
 And we don't want to be isolated.

15
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:40,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

16
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:42,760
 And wherever you go, you want that community,

17
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:44,640
 the family to welcome you.

18
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:46,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

19
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:50,080
 But in reality, sometimes it's different.

20
00:00:50,080 --> 00:00:55,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

21
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:57,280
 And sometimes we come to the United States,

22
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:59,280
 we experience different kinds of isolation.

23
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:10,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

24
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:14,320
 And all kinds of differences make us foreigner,

25
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:17,040
 whether it's religion, skin color, or culture,

26
00:01:17,040 --> 00:01:18,560
 or language.

27
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:26,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

28
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:29,360
 And sometimes in the church, we feel the same way, too.

29
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:30,960
 We are isolated from each other.

30
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:38,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

31
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:41,120
 And then we want to talk to you about a passage that

32
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:43,160
 talks about isolation and separation.

33
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:45,360
 And it's not just happened to all of us today,

34
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:47,200
 but it happened back then.

35
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:50,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

36
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:53,240
 And we talk about the church in Ephesus.

37
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:57,720
 They have different groups with hostility against each other.

38
00:01:57,720 --> 00:02:02,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

39
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:04,760
 And then this passage we're talking about,

40
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:06,720
 it talks about Christ is the only one

41
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:08,040
 who can break down the walls.

42
00:02:08,040 --> 00:02:12,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

43
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:16,480
 And that in Christ, Jesus formed a new family

44
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,960
 and new community.

45
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:20,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

46
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:23,000
 And we want to see how Christ would break down

47
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,440
 all the walls here.

48
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:28,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

49
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:32,960
 And the passage is found in Ephesians chapter 2, 11.

50
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:37,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

51
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:39,080
 There are three different divisions here.

52
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:41,480
 The first part is 11 to 12.

53
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:43,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

54
00:02:43,480 --> 00:03:08,160
 OK, 2, 11, it says, "Therefore, remember that formerly you

55
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:11,160
 are Gentiles by birth and called uncircumcised by those

56
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:13,240
 who call themselves the circumcision, which

57
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:16,000
 is done in the body by human hands.

58
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,920
 Remember that at that time you were

59
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:21,560
 separated from Christ, excluded from citizenship in Israel

60
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:24,680
 and foreigners to the covenants of the promise without hope,

61
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:27,280
 without God in the world."

62
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:30,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

63
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:33,280
 And then the second part is 13 and following.

64
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:39,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

65
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

66
00:03:42,360 --> 00:04:12,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

67
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:14,880
 Verses 13 and following, "Now in Christ Jesus,

68
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:18,640
 you who were once were far away have been brought near

69
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:20,160
 by the blood of Christ.

70
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:25,400
 And he himself is our peace, who has made the two groups one

71
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:28,280
 and has destroyed the barrier, the dividing wall of hostility

72
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:32,260
 by setting aside in his flesh the law with his commands

73
00:04:32,260 --> 00:04:33,320
 and regulations.

74
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:37,440
 His purpose was to create in himself one new humanity out

75
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:40,320
 of the two, thus making peace, and in one body

76
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:43,920
 to reconcile both of them to God through the cross by which he

77
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,960
 put to death the hostility.

78
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:48,600
 He came and preached peace to all of you

79
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:52,280
 who were far away, peace to those who were near.

80
00:04:52,280 --> 00:04:55,920
 For through him, we both have access to the Father

81
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:58,240
 by one spirit."

82
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:00,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

83
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:21,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

84
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,600
 The third division of the passage

85
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,560
 is found in verses 19 and following.

86
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:29,720
 "Consequently, so you are no longer foreigners and strangers,

87
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,920
 but fellow citizens with God's people

88
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,680
 and also members of his household,

89
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:36,800
 built on foundation of the apostles and prophets.

90
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,800
 With Christ Jesus himself as the chief cornerstone,

91
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:42,360
 in him the whole building is joined together,

92
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:45,000
 rises to become a holy temple in the Lord.

93
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,080
 In him, you too are being built together

94
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:52,120
 to become a dwelling in which God lives by the Spirit."

95
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:58,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

96
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:00,920
 And the background of this passage

97
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:04,240
 talks about the hostility between Jews and Gentiles

98
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:05,280
 in Ephesus.

99
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:07,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

100
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:09,920
 You can find the map of the city of Ephesus.

101
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:12,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

102
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:15,560
 It's located at the western side of Turkey.

103
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:19,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

104
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:23,840
 Ephesus was a metropolitan city in the ancient world.

105
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:28,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

106
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:33,400
 And on the right, you can see a humongous theater,

107
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:36,000
 and you can tell how big the city was.

108
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:42,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

109
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:44,440
 Well, not only it has great wealth,

110
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:47,880
 but it also has the famous Artemis Temple.

111
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:52,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

112
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:55,320
 And you can see the reconstruct diagram on the right.

113
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:59,640
 It has 120 marble pillars to support the temple.

114
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:07,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

115
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:09,720
 And it was a religious center of worshiping idols.

116
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:13,360
 And once in every year, the crowd

117
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:16,680
 would come from all nations to worship in festivals.

118
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:26,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

119
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:29,960
 And then there were prostitutes in the temple,

120
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:33,560
 and all the visitors would come and have

121
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:36,360
 sex with the temple prostitutes.

122
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:46,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

123
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:47,920
 And from these kind of activities,

124
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:52,480
 they thought they could guarantee fertility

125
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,360
 by doing all these things.

126
00:07:54,360 --> 00:08:04,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

127
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:07,480
 So this was the center of a pilgrimage,

128
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:09,280
 a religious idol pilgrimage.

129
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:13,880
 And that's why Ephesus was a center of economy, finance,

130
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:15,040
 and religion.

131
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:20,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

132
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:23,960
 And compared to this, even Chicago Pride Parade

133
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:26,360
 would not match this.

134
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:32,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

135
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:34,680
 So as Chicago and New York and all the major cities,

136
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:37,680
 Ephesus was a very diverse culturally.

137
00:08:37,680 --> 00:08:42,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

138
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:44,560
 So Jews and Gentiles, they lived side by side,

139
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:46,440
 and they don't like each other.

140
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:52,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

141
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,240
 And then for three years, Paul was

142
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,880
 pastoring the church in Ephesus and trying

143
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:58,960
 to break down the walls with the truth of God.

144
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:02,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

145
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:04,160
 And then the Ephesus Church will become

146
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:06,440
 a model of unity in Christ.

147
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:10,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

148
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:13,680
 And then we want to talk about what

149
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:17,040
 are the sources of hostility between the two groups.

150
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:24,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

151
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:27,320
 Paul begins by commanding the people to remember,

152
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:30,720
 and he wants them to recall their past.

153
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:38,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

154
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:40,200
 Then from the perspective of the Jews,

155
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:44,840
 the Gentiles or the foreigners were being called uncircumcised.

156
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:47,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

157
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:49,600
 So one of the sources of hostility

158
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:52,800
 is the uncircumcision of the Gentiles.

159
00:09:52,800 --> 00:10:01,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

160
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:04,200
 And from the Old Testament, you can see how important

161
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:07,960
 circumcision was, because it was our sign of God's covenant

162
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:11,080
 to his people, beginning with Abraham.

163
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:19,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

164
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:21,320
 And you can see the Bible tells us

165
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:24,480
 that circumcision is actually a symbol

166
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:27,080
 to the spiritual reality inside.

167
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:31,600
 But the Jews often turn it into a source of pride.

168
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:40,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

169
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:45,080
 They insult the Gentiles by all sorts of different racial

170
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:47,360
 insults and slurs.

171
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:56,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

172
00:10:56,880 --> 00:11:02,280
 And there were so many Roman bathrooms, which was perfect.

173
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:04,200
 And then when they see the Gentiles,

174
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:06,640
 they would despise them.

175
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:12,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

176
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:15,720
 So this kind of hostility is deeper,

177
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:19,680
 is more intense than whatever racial divide

178
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:21,040
 that we have today.

179
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:29,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

180
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,760
 So there are so many regulations among the Jews,

181
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:34,520
 and they are not willing to help Gentile women.

182
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:37,600
 Even in their childbirth, they are not willing to help them.

183
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:45,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

184
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:49,240
 And Paul was saying, you guys were being circumcised,

185
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:51,760
 but it was done by human hands.

186
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:54,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

187
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:57,360
 And Paul was a circumcised Jew as well.

188
00:11:57,360 --> 00:12:04,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

189
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:08,760
 And that's why Paul, speaking from a circumcised Jew,

190
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:13,320
 he said circumcision is merely done by a human hand.

191
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:20,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

192
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:22,200
 And then he was speaking to the Gentiles

193
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,920
 and talking to them about the fact

194
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:26,360
 that they were outside of Israel,

195
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,760
 outside of the covenant.

196
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:39,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

197
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:41,060
 So you go back to the Old Testament.

198
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:44,640
 God made a covenant with the Jews, with his people,

199
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,440
 and starting from Abraham.

200
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:50,280
 And although there were a few foreigners being included

201
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:53,760
 into the nation of Israel, but however, primarily, it

202
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,960
 was for the race, the Jews.

203
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:58,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

204
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:02,400
 So the Gentiles were the foreigners, outsiders

205
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,000
 of the covenant.

206
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:09,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

207
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:13,060
 And then all the promises belong to the Jews,

208
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:17,780
 and even the Messiah is prophesied and is for the Jews.

209
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:21,380
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

210
00:13:21,380 --> 00:13:23,380
 So that's why he says the Gentiles,

211
00:13:23,380 --> 00:13:26,940
 you have no part of this whole thing.

212
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:32,100
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

213
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:34,660
 And the Gentiles, without Christ, they have no hope.

214
00:13:34,660 --> 00:13:36,900
 They have no covenant.

215
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:44,060
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

216
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:46,700
 And you remember, we talked about Ephesus

217
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:50,720
 was a very rich city and full of wealth and temples

218
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:51,700
 and religion.

219
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:57,460
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

220
00:13:57,460 --> 00:14:00,420
 And then all the citizens in Ephesus, the Gentiles,

221
00:14:00,420 --> 00:14:03,340
 they were having nightlife and all the excitements

222
00:14:03,340 --> 00:14:05,100
 in the worldly life.

223
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:06,900
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

224
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:08,860
 And then many people would admire them

225
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:10,340
 and want to be like them.

226
00:14:10,340 --> 00:14:18,620
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

227
00:14:18,620 --> 00:14:21,140
 And Paul is talking to the Gentiles in Ephesus

228
00:14:21,140 --> 00:14:23,580
 that even though you have all of these things,

229
00:14:23,580 --> 00:14:27,460
 but you are without hope in God.

230
00:14:27,460 --> 00:14:45,900
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

231
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:49,140
 So Paul is reminding them they are totally without God,

232
00:14:49,140 --> 00:14:50,860
 without Christ, and without hope.

233
00:14:50,860 --> 00:14:53,940
 And their life may look very wealthy,

234
00:14:53,940 --> 00:14:55,940
 but their life is empty.

235
00:14:55,940 --> 00:14:59,620
 And they are without the grace of God

236
00:14:59,620 --> 00:15:02,940
 and don't part in God's program.

237
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:10,780
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

238
00:15:10,780 --> 00:15:13,060
 And one of the applications we can find in this passage

239
00:15:13,060 --> 00:15:15,900
 is that Paul's description for the Gentiles

240
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:18,780
 remind us of our own past.

241
00:15:18,780 --> 00:15:19,940
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

242
00:15:19,940 --> 00:15:21,740
 And we were foreigners.

243
00:15:21,740 --> 00:15:24,780
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

244
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:27,700
 And we were without Christ, without God, without hope.

245
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:33,420
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

246
00:15:33,420 --> 00:15:35,660
 And then to many people, maybe we

247
00:15:35,660 --> 00:15:37,860
 are having wealth and all these things in life,

248
00:15:37,860 --> 00:15:42,580
 but in the sight of God, we are without hope.

249
00:15:42,580 --> 00:15:46,260
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

250
00:15:46,260 --> 00:15:49,780
 And we can see that knowing God today, knowing Christ today,

251
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:51,820
 is entirely His grace.

252
00:15:51,820 --> 00:16:04,260
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

253
00:16:04,260 --> 00:16:06,900
 And then we can see the human nature in this passage,

254
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:09,860
 because we humans, we like to create divisions.

255
00:16:09,860 --> 00:16:12,460
 We like to focus on our differences

256
00:16:12,460 --> 00:16:13,900
 among different people.

257
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:17,500
 But God's design is not like this.

258
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:27,260
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

259
00:16:27,260 --> 00:16:31,140
 And we often use our differences to reject one another.

260
00:16:31,140 --> 00:16:34,780
 And that is actually pride, believing our group is

261
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:36,180
 superior to other groups.

262
00:16:36,180 --> 00:16:39,260
 And the Jews thought circumcision

263
00:16:39,260 --> 00:16:46,100
 made them holier so that they despised the Gentiles.

264
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:53,300
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

265
00:16:53,300 --> 00:16:56,380
 And we have to ask today whether we are building

266
00:16:56,380 --> 00:17:00,060
 this sort of invisible walls.

267
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:13,660
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

268
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:18,500
 And many differences among us in languages, in culture,

269
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,140
 in occupation.

270
00:17:20,140 --> 00:17:23,140
 Our church as well, we have English-speaking,

271
00:17:23,140 --> 00:17:25,260
 Cantonese-speaking, Mandarin-speaking people,

272
00:17:25,260 --> 00:17:30,460
 people from China, people from America, people from Hong Kong.

273
00:17:30,460 --> 00:17:43,620
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

274
00:17:43,620 --> 00:17:46,660
 Now I heard a story from a pastor that I know in Canada.

275
00:17:46,660 --> 00:17:49,740
 He said his church is filled with two groups.

276
00:17:49,740 --> 00:17:53,540
 And one group is the immigrants, investor immigrants.

277
00:17:53,540 --> 00:17:55,300
 The other group is professional immigrants.

278
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:56,960
 And they don't like each other, and they

279
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:58,980
 look down on each other.

280
00:17:58,980 --> 00:18:16,020
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

281
00:18:16,020 --> 00:18:20,460
 The professional immigrants will look down on the investors,

282
00:18:20,460 --> 00:18:21,940
 thinking that they only have money,

283
00:18:21,940 --> 00:18:24,220
 and they don't have knowledge, and they don't have

284
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:26,220
 the prestige of the society.

285
00:18:26,220 --> 00:18:30,580
 On the other hand, the investors will look down

286
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:33,860
 on the professionals and think that they are simply

287
00:18:33,860 --> 00:18:35,500
 working class people.

288
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:37,700
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

289
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:40,500
 And the church should not be like this.

290
00:18:40,500 --> 00:19:00,500
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

291
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:04,700
 Paul is trying to contrast the past and the present.

292
00:19:04,700 --> 00:19:09,100
 You were separated from God, but now you are different.

293
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:10,620
 Now you're in Christ.

294
00:19:10,620 --> 00:19:17,180
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

295
00:19:17,180 --> 00:19:21,740
 And Paul was saying, you guys were far away from God,

296
00:19:21,740 --> 00:19:24,860
 but now you are being brought near by the thought of Christ.

297
00:19:24,860 --> 00:19:31,740
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

298
00:19:31,740 --> 00:19:34,140
 And in the past, you were separated from God,

299
00:19:34,140 --> 00:19:36,220
 and now you are connected to God.

300
00:19:36,220 --> 00:19:38,300
 And that is one of the foundational change

301
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:39,740
 that we have in Christian life.

302
00:19:39,740 --> 00:19:44,980
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

303
00:19:44,980 --> 00:19:48,300
 And that is the core value of Christianity.

304
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:52,940
 You were separated from God, but now you are near to God.

305
00:19:52,940 --> 00:19:58,900
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

306
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:03,020
 And the core value, core essence of Christianity

307
00:20:03,020 --> 00:20:07,180
 is not about behavioral value change,

308
00:20:07,180 --> 00:20:11,180
 but it's about our life being changed in Christ.

309
00:20:11,180 --> 00:20:14,540
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

310
00:20:14,540 --> 00:20:16,940
 And it's not because I was bad before,

311
00:20:16,940 --> 00:20:19,420
 and now I want to improve myself, be better.

312
00:20:19,420 --> 00:20:21,380
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

313
00:20:21,380 --> 00:20:24,700
 And it is the restoration of relationship with God.

314
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:33,340
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

315
00:20:33,340 --> 00:20:39,060
 And there's one professor who was a philosopher,

316
00:20:39,060 --> 00:20:43,700
 and he used to teach in Chinese University in Hong Kong.

317
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:48,020
 He said Christianity is not about becoming a better person.

318
00:20:48,020 --> 00:20:51,540
 It is about being reconciled to God.

319
00:20:51,540 --> 00:20:56,420
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

320
00:20:56,420 --> 00:20:58,220
 And the restoration of relationship with God

321
00:20:58,220 --> 00:21:00,460
 is not about our effort.

322
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:03,940
 It's about the grace of God.

323
00:21:03,940 --> 00:21:13,940
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

324
00:21:13,940 --> 00:21:17,500
 And in Ephesus, when they worshiped the pagan god,

325
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:21,300
 that involved a lot of sacrifice and killing a lot of animals.

326
00:21:21,300 --> 00:21:26,060
 And some of the cults even practiced infant sacrifice.

327
00:21:26,060 --> 00:21:41,900
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

328
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:46,100
 And you can tell some of the pagans in the Ephesus church,

329
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:48,180
 they have that kind of background.

330
00:21:48,180 --> 00:21:52,420
 And when they heard about blood sacrifice,

331
00:21:52,420 --> 00:21:53,980
 they immediately understand.

332
00:21:53,980 --> 00:21:56,740
 But Paul is trying to say to them, all this blood

333
00:21:56,740 --> 00:21:59,300
 that you have shed before had no value

334
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:00,940
 and had no power to save you.

335
00:22:00,940 --> 00:22:05,820
 Only the blood of Jesus Christ can truly save you.

336
00:22:05,820 --> 00:22:17,340
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

337
00:22:17,340 --> 00:22:19,020
 And then what did Jesus do?

338
00:22:19,020 --> 00:22:21,740
 And he destroyed the dividing wall

339
00:22:21,740 --> 00:22:23,620
 between Jews and Gentiles.

340
00:22:23,620 --> 00:22:25,940
 And we can tell from this passage

341
00:22:25,940 --> 00:22:29,460
 what exactly Jesus has done.

342
00:22:29,460 --> 00:22:39,620
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

343
00:22:39,620 --> 00:22:42,460
 And when Paul talks about Jesus breaking down the wall,

344
00:22:42,460 --> 00:22:44,780
 he's actually referring to a physical wall that

345
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:49,380
 separates the court of the Jews and the court of the Gentiles

346
00:22:49,380 --> 00:22:50,620
 in the temple of Jerusalem.

347
00:22:50,620 --> 00:22:55,140
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

348
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:58,980
 And that wall is actually the dividing separation

349
00:22:58,980 --> 00:23:00,300
 between the Jews and Gentiles.

350
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:03,660
 And Gentiles cannot climb over the wall to go into the court.

351
00:23:03,660 --> 00:23:15,220
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

352
00:23:15,220 --> 00:23:19,180
 And we have found one of these stone inscriptions

353
00:23:19,180 --> 00:23:21,660
 that is being set up on the wall.

354
00:23:21,660 --> 00:23:23,660
 It's a warning sign to all the Gentiles.

355
00:23:23,660 --> 00:23:26,860
 And the content says, if you're Gentiles,

356
00:23:26,860 --> 00:23:30,220
 if you climb over this wall, you will bring yourself death

357
00:23:30,220 --> 00:23:31,060
 penalty.

358
00:23:31,060 --> 00:23:38,420
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

359
00:23:38,420 --> 00:23:41,940
 So Paul is saying, Jesus came to break down this wall.

360
00:23:41,940 --> 00:23:44,460
 Exactly, this wall is trying to break down so

361
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:47,860
 that Jews and Gentiles are one.

362
00:23:47,860 --> 00:23:54,820
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

363
00:23:54,820 --> 00:23:58,660
 And when he talks about the regulations and the commandments,

364
00:23:58,660 --> 00:24:02,420
 he talks about the commandments received by the Jews from God.

365
00:24:02,420 --> 00:24:13,540
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

366
00:24:13,540 --> 00:24:18,020
 And because Jesus came, the Jews and even the Gentiles,

367
00:24:18,020 --> 00:24:21,740
 we do not depend on the sacrifice from the animal,

368
00:24:21,740 --> 00:24:24,780
 because Jesus is the perfect sacrifice.

369
00:24:24,780 --> 00:24:33,420
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

370
00:24:33,420 --> 00:24:35,740
 Now, the source of the law of Moses

371
00:24:35,740 --> 00:24:37,740
 is actually from the grace of God.

372
00:24:37,740 --> 00:24:39,780
 And God has given the law so that the people

373
00:24:39,780 --> 00:24:42,900
 would behave in such a way that would match their identity.

374
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:47,500
 However, the irony is that sometimes the Jews and people

375
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:50,260
 would focus on, because we are keeping the law,

376
00:24:50,260 --> 00:24:52,620
 that's why we are better than other people.

377
00:24:52,620 --> 00:24:58,620
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

378
00:24:58,620 --> 00:25:00,980
 And just like the Pharisees, they

379
00:25:00,980 --> 00:25:04,420
 were trying to accuse Jesus of not keeping the law,

380
00:25:04,420 --> 00:25:07,300
 and not keeping the law just like them.

381
00:25:07,300 --> 00:25:10,580
 That's why they accused Jesus and tried to kill him.

382
00:25:10,580 --> 00:25:20,140
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

383
00:25:20,140 --> 00:25:21,900
 And that's why the law, Paul says,

384
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:26,820
 the Jews and the Gentiles divide different groups of people.

385
00:25:26,820 --> 00:25:30,740
 And Jesus came to remove the barrier,

386
00:25:30,740 --> 00:25:35,140
 because Jesus is the perfect keeper of the law.

387
00:25:35,140 --> 00:25:42,540
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

388
00:25:42,540 --> 00:25:45,540
 And Christ fulfilled the law in every single level,

389
00:25:45,540 --> 00:25:49,500
 removing the law as a barrier between different people.

390
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:55,940
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

391
00:25:55,940 --> 00:26:00,220
 And that in Christ, in Jesus, we are created as one new humanity.

392
00:26:00,220 --> 00:26:04,940
 Jews and Gentiles are all one, united in Christ.

393
00:26:04,940 --> 00:26:10,340
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

394
00:26:10,340 --> 00:26:12,940
 So the Bible is telling us the cross of Jesus

395
00:26:12,940 --> 00:26:16,020
 is the foundation of true peace.

396
00:26:16,020 --> 00:26:21,460
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

397
00:26:21,460 --> 00:26:25,060
 And the true unity between different kinds of people

398
00:26:25,060 --> 00:26:29,580
 begins and founded on the peace of Christ.

399
00:26:29,580 --> 00:26:31,620
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

400
00:26:31,620 --> 00:26:33,740
 So if there was no peace of cross,

401
00:26:33,740 --> 00:26:36,540
 there was no harmony between different kinds of people.

402
00:26:36,540 --> 00:26:44,820
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

403
00:26:44,820 --> 00:26:47,060
 So Paul is trying to emphasize the fact

404
00:26:47,060 --> 00:26:49,220
 that Jews or Gentiles, whether you

405
00:26:49,220 --> 00:26:51,500
 belong to the first group or the second group,

406
00:26:51,500 --> 00:26:56,380
 you have to come to Christ, come to God through Jesus Christ.

407
00:26:56,380 --> 00:27:07,380
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

408
00:27:07,380 --> 00:27:09,580
 And if we want to resolve conflicts

409
00:27:09,580 --> 00:27:13,540
 between different people, we must come to the cross

410
00:27:13,540 --> 00:27:16,500
 and meet Jesus at the foot of the cross,

411
00:27:16,500 --> 00:27:20,020
 because we are all sinners and we need the grace of God.

412
00:27:20,020 --> 00:27:22,700
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

413
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:25,420
 And if you want to make peace with yourself,

414
00:27:25,420 --> 00:27:29,900
 you have to find the true peace in Jesus first.

415
00:27:29,900 --> 00:27:36,340
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

416
00:27:36,340 --> 00:27:38,860
 And sometimes we cannot make peace with ourselves

417
00:27:38,860 --> 00:27:40,700
 because we cannot forgive ourselves,

418
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:45,500
 but we find true forgiveness only in Jesus Christ.

419
00:27:45,500 --> 00:27:52,340
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

420
00:27:52,340 --> 00:27:55,980
 And then this passage tells us the three persons of the Trinity,

421
00:27:55,980 --> 00:28:00,860
 the same God, all participate in the reconciliation of mankind

422
00:28:00,860 --> 00:28:02,540
 relationship with God.

423
00:28:02,540 --> 00:28:06,140
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

424
00:28:06,140 --> 00:28:08,820
 And Paul says, through the Spirit, we come to the Father.

425
00:28:08,820 --> 00:28:12,700
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

426
00:28:12,700 --> 00:28:16,580
 And the Son redeems us and the Spirit makes us one.

427
00:28:16,580 --> 00:28:20,940
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

428
00:28:20,940 --> 00:28:24,500
 So we talk about Father's love and the redemption of Christ,

429
00:28:24,500 --> 00:28:29,020
 and we also emphasize the Spirit's work in our lives.

430
00:28:29,020 --> 00:28:31,980
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

431
00:28:31,980 --> 00:28:35,260
 So Christianity is not just doctrine, not just knowledge,

432
00:28:35,260 --> 00:28:38,980
 but it involves power, life-changing power

433
00:28:38,980 --> 00:28:39,780
 in the Spirit.

434
00:28:39,780 --> 00:28:48,140
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

435
00:28:48,140 --> 00:28:49,940
 So the doctrines that we believe in

436
00:28:49,940 --> 00:28:54,020
 is founded in the historic event of Jesus Christ.

437
00:28:54,020 --> 00:28:58,140
 And without what Jesus has done, our doctrine will be empty.

438
00:28:58,140 --> 00:29:02,500
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

439
00:29:02,500 --> 00:29:05,540
 But if we just have doctrine and theology without the Spirit,

440
00:29:05,540 --> 00:29:10,340
 it becomes dead faith, dead orthodoxy.

441
00:29:10,340 --> 00:29:14,100
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

442
00:29:14,100 --> 00:29:17,860
 But if we just pursue the Spirit without the truth,

443
00:29:17,860 --> 00:29:21,940
 it will become unhealthy emotionalism in our faith.

444
00:29:21,940 --> 00:29:27,100
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

445
00:29:27,100 --> 00:29:28,700
 And we need both truth and the Spirit.

446
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:34,140
 And one of the main ways is to rely on the Spirit

447
00:29:34,140 --> 00:29:36,580
 through our prayer.

448
00:29:36,580 --> 00:29:41,300
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

449
00:29:41,300 --> 00:29:43,500
 And we can pray anytime.

450
00:29:43,500 --> 00:29:47,420
 And the irony is that sometimes we don't pray.

451
00:29:47,420 --> 00:29:54,980
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

452
00:29:54,980 --> 00:29:57,660
 And sometimes we find it easy to attend worship,

453
00:29:57,660 --> 00:30:00,540
 to give an offering, but praying sometimes

454
00:30:00,540 --> 00:30:02,260
 becomes difficult for all of us.

455
00:30:02,260 --> 00:30:09,980
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

456
00:30:09,980 --> 00:30:12,100
 We can talk to our friend and have

457
00:30:12,100 --> 00:30:13,660
 chat with our friend for hours.

458
00:30:13,660 --> 00:30:16,300
 But sometimes the moment comes we have to pray.

459
00:30:16,300 --> 00:30:19,020
 Sometimes our minds will wander.

460
00:30:19,020 --> 00:30:25,060
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

461
00:30:25,060 --> 00:30:27,260
 And different things will occupy our mind.

462
00:30:27,260 --> 00:30:28,980
 And we cannot be silent.

463
00:30:28,980 --> 00:30:32,540
 We cannot be attentive before God and pray.

464
00:30:32,540 --> 00:30:34,420
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

465
00:30:34,420 --> 00:30:36,780
 And after a few minutes, we give up praying.

466
00:30:36,780 --> 00:30:38,460
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

467
00:30:38,460 --> 00:30:43,340
 So we need the Spirit to help us to pray.

468
00:30:43,340 --> 00:30:46,420
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

469
00:30:46,420 --> 00:30:48,300
 So the third point here--

470
00:30:48,300 --> 00:30:49,860
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

471
00:30:49,860 --> 00:31:01,500
 So you were separated from Christ,

472
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:03,620
 but Jesus came to break down all this wall.

473
00:31:03,620 --> 00:31:06,900
 And you are now near to Christ.

474
00:31:06,900 --> 00:31:08,140
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

475
00:31:08,140 --> 00:31:26,980
 So the different identity changes here.

476
00:31:26,980 --> 00:31:30,180
 From you were foreigners, and now you

477
00:31:30,180 --> 00:31:32,220
 are fellow citizens in the kingdom.

478
00:31:32,220 --> 00:31:33,780
 You were strangers to God.

479
00:31:33,780 --> 00:31:37,020
 Now you are members of the family, the household of God.

480
00:31:37,020 --> 00:31:39,620
 You were scattered stone and separated, isolated.

481
00:31:39,620 --> 00:31:43,100
 But now you have been built together to become a temple.

482
00:31:43,100 --> 00:31:47,660
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

483
00:31:47,660 --> 00:31:51,260
 And then before, we did not have the heavenly identity.

484
00:31:51,260 --> 00:31:53,780
 Now we do have the heavenly identity in the kingdom.

485
00:31:53,780 --> 00:31:58,500
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

486
00:31:58,500 --> 00:32:01,140
 In the past, we wandered without hope.

487
00:32:01,140 --> 00:32:03,540
 But now we are part of the family,

488
00:32:03,540 --> 00:32:06,060
 part of the God's household.

489
00:32:06,060 --> 00:32:10,860
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

490
00:32:10,860 --> 00:32:14,540
 And we are all part of the members

491
00:32:14,540 --> 00:32:17,460
 being built together to build the dwelling of God,

492
00:32:17,460 --> 00:32:19,220
 the temple of God.

493
00:32:19,220 --> 00:32:24,780
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

494
00:32:24,780 --> 00:32:28,780
 So the church is actually God's temple in construction.

495
00:32:28,780 --> 00:32:32,540
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

496
00:32:32,540 --> 00:32:35,220
 And the church refers not to the physical building here,

497
00:32:35,220 --> 00:32:38,140
 but the people of God themselves.

498
00:32:38,140 --> 00:32:50,940
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

499
00:32:50,940 --> 00:32:52,980
 Of course, our church is a visible church,

500
00:32:52,980 --> 00:32:55,020
 a manifestation of the people of God.

501
00:32:55,020 --> 00:32:57,460
 But there is also a capital C church,

502
00:32:57,460 --> 00:33:00,860
 which is so much bigger and involves all the saints

503
00:33:00,860 --> 00:33:02,420
 and all the Christians from history

504
00:33:02,420 --> 00:33:06,220
 and from different parts of the world.

505
00:33:06,220 --> 00:33:21,860
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

506
00:33:21,860 --> 00:33:25,260
 So the capital C church is the invisible church, which is real

507
00:33:25,260 --> 00:33:29,220
 and involves all the Christians from all the times.

508
00:33:29,220 --> 00:33:33,500
 And it goes beyond geographical boundaries.

509
00:33:33,500 --> 00:33:37,620
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

510
00:33:37,620 --> 00:33:42,300
 So it says the church has a cornerstone in Christ.

511
00:33:42,300 --> 00:33:44,660
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

512
00:33:44,660 --> 00:33:47,940
 And I find this diagram.

513
00:33:47,940 --> 00:33:51,780
 It shows you the cornerstone, where it is.

514
00:33:51,780 --> 00:33:56,060
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

515
00:33:56,060 --> 00:33:59,460
 And the foundation is the apostles and the prophets.

516
00:33:59,460 --> 00:34:00,980
 It's on the wall here.

517
00:34:00,980 --> 00:34:03,900
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

518
00:34:03,900 --> 00:34:06,260
 So the cornerstone, you see, is Jesus Christ.

519
00:34:06,260 --> 00:34:08,860
 And the wall connected to the cornerstone

520
00:34:08,860 --> 00:34:12,380
 is the prophet and the apostles.

521
00:34:12,380 --> 00:34:16,260
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

522
00:34:16,260 --> 00:34:21,340
 And that's why all the Christians from the entire world,

523
00:34:21,340 --> 00:34:23,620
 we are part of this house.

524
00:34:23,620 --> 00:34:30,740
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

525
00:34:30,740 --> 00:34:35,460
 And the importance of the cornerstone, because it

526
00:34:35,460 --> 00:34:38,300
 dictates the plan and the structure

527
00:34:38,300 --> 00:34:39,900
 of the entire building.

528
00:34:39,900 --> 00:34:41,860
 And that is Jesus Christ himself.

529
00:34:41,860 --> 00:34:46,700
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

530
00:34:46,700 --> 00:34:50,700
 And church is not built by a man.

531
00:34:50,700 --> 00:34:54,060
 It's not just a social organization.

532
00:34:54,060 --> 00:35:03,300
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

533
00:35:03,300 --> 00:35:05,900
 And if the church is simply a social organization,

534
00:35:05,900 --> 00:35:07,740
 it would not survive for so many years.

535
00:35:07,740 --> 00:35:09,300
 But you can tell from church history,

536
00:35:09,300 --> 00:35:12,460
 the church survives all the generations.

537
00:35:12,460 --> 00:35:17,460
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

538
00:35:17,460 --> 00:35:20,620
 And the church is founded on Jesus Christ, the cornerstone,

539
00:35:20,620 --> 00:35:24,140
 and Christ himself dictates and commands the church.

540
00:35:24,140 --> 00:35:42,740
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

541
00:35:42,740 --> 00:35:47,220
 And you can see, even our church, sometimes we decline.

542
00:35:47,220 --> 00:35:50,420
 And our church can fall apart.

543
00:35:50,420 --> 00:35:53,060
 But we have to have that perspective of the capital C

544
00:35:53,060 --> 00:35:55,580
 Church, and Christ is commanding his church,

545
00:35:55,580 --> 00:35:58,580
 and all of the world, and all through history.

546
00:35:58,580 --> 00:36:11,180
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

547
00:36:11,180 --> 00:36:13,620
 And every member of the church, every Christian,

548
00:36:13,620 --> 00:36:17,900
 is one of the living stones being built together

549
00:36:17,900 --> 00:36:20,380
 to form the temple for God.

550
00:36:20,380 --> 00:36:25,100
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

551
00:36:25,100 --> 00:36:28,740
 So in this diagram, we are part of the different stones

552
00:36:28,740 --> 00:36:30,940
 and bricks to build this whole household.

553
00:36:30,940 --> 00:36:44,300
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

554
00:36:44,300 --> 00:36:46,940
 And you can see the church will continue

555
00:36:46,940 --> 00:36:48,780
 to grow no matter what.

556
00:36:48,780 --> 00:36:50,580
 If you include the Old Testament,

557
00:36:50,580 --> 00:36:52,540
 it has even longer history.

558
00:36:52,540 --> 00:36:56,380
 And the church will continue to grow.

559
00:36:56,380 --> 00:36:59,900
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

560
00:36:59,900 --> 00:37:03,540
 And the church will continue to grow in the size

561
00:37:03,540 --> 00:37:06,020
 that's beyond our imagination.

562
00:37:06,020 --> 00:37:15,660
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

563
00:37:15,660 --> 00:37:19,700
 And for now, church history seems

564
00:37:19,700 --> 00:37:22,780
 to be mixed with the world history.

565
00:37:22,780 --> 00:37:28,300
 But it seems like it's just one of the organizations

566
00:37:28,300 --> 00:37:29,580
 in the world.

567
00:37:29,580 --> 00:37:38,940
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

568
00:37:38,940 --> 00:37:41,420
 But you have to remember the church is in construction.

569
00:37:41,420 --> 00:37:43,900
 And you can tell, if an unfinished building,

570
00:37:43,900 --> 00:37:46,300
 you can see a lot of different things here,

571
00:37:46,300 --> 00:37:51,060
 different unconstructed part, and needs to be renovated.

572
00:37:51,060 --> 00:37:55,900
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

573
00:37:55,900 --> 00:37:58,060
 But this building will continue to grow

574
00:37:58,060 --> 00:38:00,500
 and continue to be constructed by Christ.

575
00:38:00,500 --> 00:38:04,100
 And someday, this church will be complete.

576
00:38:04,100 --> 00:38:07,500
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

577
00:38:07,500 --> 00:38:10,540
 And then all these tools and unfinished part will be gone.

578
00:38:10,540 --> 00:38:11,940
 And the wall will be gone.

579
00:38:11,940 --> 00:38:13,140
 But the church remains.

580
00:38:13,140 --> 00:38:27,060
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

581
00:38:27,060 --> 00:38:30,100
 And it seems that the church is growing

582
00:38:30,100 --> 00:38:33,940
 with all kinds of organizations in the world, all the bodies

583
00:38:33,940 --> 00:38:34,540
 in the world.

584
00:38:34,540 --> 00:38:36,700
 But someday, when God completes His church,

585
00:38:36,700 --> 00:38:41,140
 everything will be unnecessary and will be removed.

586
00:38:41,140 --> 00:38:46,020
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

587
00:38:46,020 --> 00:38:48,380
 And you can see we are the church.

588
00:38:48,380 --> 00:38:50,180
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

589
00:38:50,180 --> 00:38:54,020
 The Spirit of God lives among us.

590
00:38:54,020 --> 00:39:08,100
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

591
00:39:08,100 --> 00:39:10,340
 You think about it in the Old Testament,

592
00:39:10,340 --> 00:39:13,300
 when the people of God want to see God and worship God,

593
00:39:13,300 --> 00:39:15,340
 they have to travel a long distance

594
00:39:15,340 --> 00:39:18,860
 to come to the temple to worship God together.

595
00:39:18,860 --> 00:39:23,420
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

596
00:39:23,420 --> 00:39:26,460
 But now Christ has come.

597
00:39:26,460 --> 00:39:29,340
 All the people of God lives in Christ Himself.

598
00:39:29,340 --> 00:39:33,980
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

599
00:39:33,980 --> 00:39:38,020
 So each and every one of us, the Spirit lives among us.

600
00:39:38,020 --> 00:39:42,660
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

601
00:39:42,660 --> 00:39:46,140
 So when we love each other and we care for each other,

602
00:39:46,140 --> 00:39:50,260
 the light of God will be demonstrated.

603
00:39:50,260 --> 00:39:59,020
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

604
00:39:59,020 --> 00:40:02,660
 And if we think about it, we need

605
00:40:02,660 --> 00:40:04,740
 to ask the question whether we are still

606
00:40:04,740 --> 00:40:07,860
 having the mentality of foreigners or outsiders.

607
00:40:07,860 --> 00:40:10,580
 We don't find the sense of belonging here.

608
00:40:10,580 --> 00:40:17,420
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

609
00:40:17,420 --> 00:40:20,940
 But you have to remember, even though you don't find acceptance

610
00:40:20,940 --> 00:40:23,540
 in the community, you have to remember

611
00:40:23,540 --> 00:40:27,180
 that you are fully accepted in Christ Jesus.

612
00:40:27,180 --> 00:40:34,300
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

613
00:40:34,300 --> 00:40:38,860
 And when Christ sees you, it's not because of your skin color,

614
00:40:38,860 --> 00:40:40,380
 it's not because of your background,

615
00:40:40,380 --> 00:40:43,980
 but sees you just like He sees you in Christ, in Jesus.

616
00:40:43,980 --> 00:40:48,220
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

617
00:40:48,220 --> 00:40:51,100
 So your identity now you find in Christ

618
00:40:51,100 --> 00:40:53,380
 is that you are part of the family of God

619
00:40:53,380 --> 00:40:56,900
 and part of the people of God and near to God.

620
00:40:56,900 --> 00:41:00,300
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

621
00:41:00,300 --> 00:41:01,940
 And that's why we need to pray and we

622
00:41:01,940 --> 00:41:06,220
 need to dwell in the presence of God, to draw near to Him.

623
00:41:06,220 --> 00:41:08,300
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

624
00:41:08,300 --> 00:41:10,260
 Let's all pray together.

625
00:41:10,260 --> 00:41:12,780
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

626
00:41:12,780 --> 00:41:16,260
 Heavenly Father, we want to praise you and give you thanks.

627
00:41:16,260 --> 00:41:19,100
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

628
00:41:19,100 --> 00:41:22,780
 You sent Jesus, your son, to be the messenger of peace.

629
00:41:22,780 --> 00:41:24,660
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

630
00:41:24,660 --> 00:41:27,980
 So that we can restore our relationship with you.

631
00:41:27,980 --> 00:41:32,540
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

632
00:41:32,540 --> 00:41:34,460
 And we are no longer outsiders and we

633
00:41:34,460 --> 00:41:38,340
 can come become your family and call you Abba Father.

634
00:41:38,340 --> 00:41:42,020
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

635
00:41:42,020 --> 00:41:45,100
 Our Savior, Jesus Christ, He broke down all the barriers

636
00:41:45,100 --> 00:41:45,900
 with His blood.

637
00:41:45,900 --> 00:41:48,260
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

638
00:41:48,260 --> 00:41:50,460
 And we are all different in front of you.

639
00:41:50,460 --> 00:41:52,580
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

640
00:41:52,580 --> 00:41:56,580
 And I just pray that you will help us to be united in you.

641
00:41:56,580 --> 00:42:02,020
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

642
00:42:02,020 --> 00:42:04,900
 And help us not forget that we are all sinners

643
00:42:04,900 --> 00:42:06,660
 and we are not better than other people.

644
00:42:06,660 --> 00:42:07,900
 We are all saved by grace.

645
00:42:07,900 --> 00:42:10,300
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

646
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:13,980
 And please make us peacemakers as well.

647
00:42:13,980 --> 00:42:17,620
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

648
00:42:17,620 --> 00:42:20,900
 So that we can bring the message of reconciliation

649
00:42:20,900 --> 00:42:22,420
 to other people.

650
00:42:22,420 --> 00:42:24,180
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

651
00:42:24,180 --> 00:42:25,500
 In Jesus' name we pray.

652
00:42:25,500 --> 00:42:26,000
 Amen.

653
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:26,840
 Bye.

654
00:42:26,840 --> 00:42:30,180
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

